      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260519003103.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] Scientists found a smarter Mediterranean diet that slashes diabetes risk by 31%",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nA large European study revealed that a lower-calorie Mediterranean diet paired with exercise and coaching dramatically reduced the risk of type 2 diabetes. Participants who made these lifestyle changes were 31% less likely to develop the disease over six years. They also lost more weight and trimmed their waistlines compared to those following a standard Mediterranean diet alone.",
